 {
  "key": "fanout",
  "title": "Dense fan-out — distinct anchors + outer lanes",
  "subtitle": "Untangling N edges that fan from one node and N edges that converge on one node — the two moves the auto-router can't always make for you",
  "desc": "A processor fans a write to three stacked stores, then two of them converge on a rollup dashboard. The renderer keeps wires orthogonal on its own, but on a dense plane edges that share a side co-run or slice an icon. The fix is always in the spec, never the SVG.",
