  ],
  "notes": "The two anti-tangle moves shown here. (1) FAN-OUT (proc -> a/b/c): each edge leaves a DISTINCT source anchor (ss = tr / r / br) so the three writes separate right at the node boundary instead of stacking on one side; the long top/bottom edges then ride their own outer lane via [[660,150]] / [[660,510]] so they don't co-run with the short middle hop. (2) CONVERGE (a + b -> dash): the two reads enter the rollup on DIFFERENT sides (b on the left, a on the top via [[1180,230]]) so they don't co-run into one anchor. Both are spec-only fixes (ss/ds/via) — re-render, never hand-edit the SVG."
